column4: hi guys, when i try to install mplayer from synapitc, im getting this error,... Package mplayer-386 has no available version, but exists in the database.
thanks, whats the difference between 386, 586, 686, etc?
Package mplayer-586 is not available, but is referred to by another package.
try to use "sudo apt-get install mplayer", lets see all the candidates available for mplayer
ive already enabled multiverse, and universe
what ubuntu release are you using, state the processor + version of ubuntu
do "apt-cache search mplayer" for me, see what its output
there is no "mplayer" package in your system right now
all of them, i enabled the disabled ones in the settings, and then ticked all the repositories
i forgot to add multiverse to the universe repositories:)
